<div class="wallpaper wallpaper-resources">
    <div class="resource-container" uk-grid>
        {{!-- Be Whale Wise --}}
        <div class="resource-card uk-card uk-card-default uk-card-hover uk-child-width-1-2@m" uk-grid>
            <div class="logo-div uk-card-media-top uk-cover-container">
                <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/be-whale-wise-logo.png" alt="Be Whale Wise Logo">
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="uk-card-body">
                    <h3 class="uk-card-title"><a href="https://www.bewhalewise.org/" target="_blank"><span class="link" uk-icon="link"></span></a>Be Whale Wise</h3>
                    <p>Learn about laws and guidelines pertaining to our local marine mammals in order to find out what you can do to keep these magnificent creatures safe.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        {{!-- Whale Museum --}}
        <div class="resource-card uk-card uk-card-default uk-card-hover uk-child-width-1-2@m" uk-grid>
            <div class="logo-div uk-card-media-top uk-cover-container">
                <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/wm-logo-sm.png" alt="Whale Museum Logo">
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="uk-card-body">
                    <h3 class="uk-card-title"><a href="https://whalemuseum.org/" target="_blank"><span class="link" uk-icon="link"></span></a>Whale Museum, Friday Harbor</h3>
                    <p>A museum focused on continuous education and research regarding our local marine wildlife, especially the Southern Resident orcas, who are on the endangered species list. They have an ongoing donation project where you can <a href="https://whalemuseum.org/collections/adopt-an-orca" target="_blank">Adopt an orca</a>. You can also find them on the west side of San Juan Island at Lime Kiln State Park, where they have a lighthouse set up as a research lab with a <a href="https://whalemuseum.org/pages/seasound-remote-sensing-network" target="_blank">hydrophone</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        {{!-- Orca Network --}}
        <div class="resource-card uk-card uk-card-default uk-card-hover uk-child-width-1-2@m" uk-grid>
            <div class="logo-div uk-card-media-top uk-cover-container">
                <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/orca-network-logo.jpg" alt="Orca Network Logo">
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="uk-card-body">
                    <h3 class="uk-card-title"><a href="http://www.orcanetwork.org/Main/" target="_blank"><span class="link" uk-icon="link"></span></a>Orca Network</h3>
                    <p>A non-profit organization located on Whidbey Island who is bringing awareness and informing the public about ways to help keep our Pacific Northwest whales safe and healthy. They have volunteer projects available and work in conjunction with the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/LangleyWhaleCenter" target="_blank">Langley Whale Center</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        {{!-- The Whale Trail --}}
        <div class="resource-card uk-card uk-card-default uk-card-hover uk-child-width-1-2@m" uk-grid>
            <div class="logo-div uk-card-media-top uk-cover-container">
                <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/whale-trail-logo.jpg" alt="The Whale Trail Logo">
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="uk-card-body">
                    <h3 class="uk-card-title"><a href="https://thewhaletrail.org/" target="_blank"><span class="link" uk-icon="link"></span></a>The Whale Trail</h3>
                    <p>Set along the Pacific Coast from California to British Columbia, the Whale Trail is a compilation of over 100 shoreline sites to view the marine wildlife. They hope to inspire others to whale-watch from the shore and to gain an appreciation of orcas and other marine mammals, in hopes of fully recovering the Southern Resident Orca population.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        {{!-- Center for Whale Research --}}
        <div class="resource-card uk-card uk-card-default uk-card-hover uk-child-width-1-2@m" uk-grid>
            <div class="logo-div uk-card-media-top uk-cover-container">
                <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/center-whale-research-logo.jpeg" alt="Center for Whale Research Logo">
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="uk-card-body">
                    <h3 class="uk-card-title"><a href="https://www.whaleresearch.com/" target="_blank"><span class="link" uk-icon="link"></span></a>Center for Whale Research, Friday Harbor</h3>
                    <p>A group dedicated to daily and annual studies of the local Southern Resident orcas, in hopes of bringing them off the endangered species list. In a recent conservation effort, they purchased a 45-acre ranch along the Elwha River, aimed at preserving the Chinook salmon habitat, the primary source of food for the local orcas.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        {{!-- WA Dept of Fish and Wildlife --}}
        <div class="resource-card uk-card uk-card-default uk-card-hover uk-child-width-1-2@m" uk-grid>
            <div class="logo-div uk-card-media-top uk-cover-container">
                <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/fish-wildlife-logo.jpg" alt="WA Deparment of Fish and Wildlife Logo">
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="uk-card-body">
                    <h3 class="uk-card-title"><a href="https://wdfw.wa.gov/species-habitats/at-risk/species-recovery/orca" target="_blank"><span class="link" uk-icon="link"></span></a>Washington Department of Fish and Wildlife - Orca Conservation</h3>
                    <p>Learn about the endangered Southern Resident orcas, what threats are prevelant, the progress being made to aid our residents and what you can do to help!</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        {{!-- WA State Dept of Ecology --}}
        <div class="resource-card uk-card uk-card-default uk-card-hover uk-child-width-1-2@m" uk-grid>
            <div class="logo-div uk-card-media-top uk-cover-container">
                <img class="logo-img" src="/images/logos/dept-ecology-logo.png" alt="Department of Ecology WA State Logo">
            </div>
            <div>
                <div class="uk-card-body">
                    <h3 class="uk-card-title"><a href="https://ecology.wa.gov/Water-Shorelines/Puget-Sound/Orca-task-force" target="_blank"><span class="link" uk-icon="link"></span></a>Department of Ecology, Washington State - Orca Task Force</h3>
                    <p>A group focused on studying, protecting and improving the environment surrounding the marine mammals, especially the Southern Resident Orcas. Here, you can read about their findings and their recommendations for short-term and long-term actions, both from elected officials and what you can do to help.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>